37\. And on account of the procedure, on the ascertainment of the
non-being of that.

That a *S*ûdra is not qualified for knowledge of Brahman appears from
that fact also that as soon as Gautama has convinced himself that
*G*âbâla, who wishes to become his pupil, is not a *S*ûdra, he proceeds
to teach him the knowledge of Brahman.

